Package: inferlab
Type: Package
Title: Statistical Inference Tools for Estimation, Testing, and Information
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Sagar", "S", email = "sagars314@proton.me", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A toolkit for classical statistical inference based on the
    MTH418 curriculum. Provides functions for exponential families,
    sufficient statistics, completeness, unbiased estimation via
    Rao-Blackwell and Lehmann-Scheffe methods, information inequalities
    such as Cramer-Rao and Bhattacharyya bounds, estimation methods
    including method of moments and minimum mean square error, hypothesis
    testing procedures such as Neyman-Pearson, UMP, UMPU, and likelihood
    ratio tests, and confidence intervals including UMA, UMAU, and
    shortest-length intervals.
